19/11/2004
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The government expressed readiness for talks with trade unions after mass protests Thursday (18 November). Around 400,000 people took part in one-hour rallies held in Sofia and other major cities, demanding a salary hike and benefits. Later Thursday, the cabinet said it was prepared to discuss the demands. (Sega - 19/11/04; bTV, Bulgarian National Radio - 18/11/04)
